wiki.summary: "Hurry Up Tomorrow" is the closing track on The Weeknd's sixth studio album of the same name, released on January 31, 2025. This song serves as a poignant conclusion to both the album and The Weeknd's trilogy that includes "After Hours" and "Dawn FM." In "Hurry Up Tomorrow," The Weeknd reflects on themes of personal transformation, regret, and his deep yearning for redemption. The song follows his emotional journey as he realizes the consequences of his actions, struggles with regret, and longs for a fresh start. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Hurry Up Tomorrow" is the closing track on The Weeknd's sixth studio album of the same name, released on January 31, 2025. This song serves as a poignant conclusion to both the album and The Weeknd's trilogy that includes "After Hours" and "Dawn FM." In "Hurry Up Tomorrow," The Weeknd reflects on themes of personal transformation, regret, and his deep yearning for redemption. The song follows his emotional journey as he realizes the consequences of his actions, struggles with regret, and longs for a fresh start. It serves as a farewell to his former self, symbolizing a transformation and a desire to leave behind pain and be rebirthed . He also accepts the severity of his past hedonistic actions and plans to change it. The Weeknd is finally becoming a better person and turning over a new leaf. The track closes The Weeknd’s trilogy by marking the end of his alter ego and the beginning of a new chapter as Abel Tesfaye Read more on Last.fm.
